-- OPIC to Invest $175 Million in Two Renewable Energy Funds
-- B y   A n d r e w   H e r n d o n
-- 2012-06-19T23:04:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-19/opic-to-invest-175-million-in-two-renewable-energy-funds.html
The Overseas Private Investment
Corp. will invest $175 million in two renewable energy funds
managed by TPG Capital and GEF Management Corp.  TPG’s Alternative & Renewable Technologies Partners will
receive $125 million and invest in U.S. and European companies
that deploy clean energy technologies in  Latin America  and
 Southeast Asia , OPIC, an independent U.S. government agency
based in Washington, D.C., said today in a statement.  GEF’s Africa Growth Fund will receive $50 million and
invest in renewable power and energy efficiency technologies in
sub-Saharan Africa as well as companies that promote sustainable
agriculture, OPIC said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Charles Siler at 
 csiler@bloomberg.net  